  "text": "Ferrets were deprived of food overnight. Copper sulfate solution (40 mg / kg) was rapidly flushed into the stomach via an orogastric tube, as previously described [CITATION_1] . Animals were observed continuously for 30 min for emetic responses, the time of onset to retching or vomiting, and the number of both retches and vomits. FK1052 (3.2 mg / kg), granisetron (3.2 mg / kg), or vehicle (1 ml / kg) was intravenously administered through a forelimb (cephalic) vein 5 min before the administration of copper sulfate.",
